'''''Vanmam''''' ({{lang-en|Vengeance}}) is a 2014 Indian [[Tamil cinema|Tamil]] action drama film directed by Jai Krishna, a former assistant of [[Kamal Haasan]].<ref name="indiatimes1">{{cite news|url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/regional/tamil/news-interviews/Vijay-Sethupathi-Kreshna-become-friends/articleshow/22289899.cms?referral=PM |title=Vijay Sethupathi, Kreshna become friends |newspaper=[[The Times of India]]|author=V. Lakshmi |date=5 September 2013 |accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref> It features [[Vijay Sethupathi]], [[Kreshna]] and [[Sunaina]] in the lead roles.<ref name = TNIE>{{cite news|url=http://www.newindianexpress.com/entertainment/tamil/Vijay-Sethupathis-Vanmam-kicks-off/2014/04/30/article2196520.ece |title=Vijay Sethupathi's 'Vanmam' kicks off |newspaper=[[The New Indian Express]] |date=30 April 2014|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref> The film has music scored by [[S. Thaman]] and cinematography by Balabharani.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/article/106827.html |title=Vijay Sethupathi's film commences in Kanyakumari |publisher=''Indiaglitz'' |date=29 April 2014|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref><ref name="thehindu1">{{cite news|url=http://www.thehindu.com/features/cinema/cinema-columns/udhayanidhi-ropes-in-ahmed-to-direct-his-next/article5918875.ece |title=Udhayanidhi ropes in Ahmed to direct his next |newspaper=[[The Hindu]]|author=Naig, Udhav |date=16 April 2014 |accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref> It is a rural tale about the life of two friends, played by Sethupathi and Kreshna.<ref name="indiatimes1"/><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.indiaglitz.com/vijay-sethupathi-is-a-ruffian-in-vanmam-tamil-news-106313 |title=Vijay Sethupathi is a ruffian in 'Vanmam' |publisher=''Indiaglitz'' |date=17 April 2014|accessdate=30 April 2014}}</ref> In spite of expectations the movie didn't perform well at the box office. The film was highly panned by the critics for its poor screenplay. The satellite rights of the film were bagged by [[Raj TV]]

