[[S. Thaman]] composed the music for the film. The audio launch of the film was scheduled to take place on 28 August 2014,<ref>[http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/entertainment/tamil/music/Vanmam-audio-launch-on-August-28/articleshow/40581784.cms "'Vanmam' audio launch on August 28"]. ''[[The Times of India]]''. 21 August 2014. Retrieved 2 September 2014.</ref> but was postponed to 2 September 2014. The audio rights were purchased by [[Sony Music India]].<ref>[http://tamil.way2movies.com//newssingle_tamil/Vanmam-audio-launch-on-Sep-2-4-308177.html "'Vanmam' audio launch on Sep 2"]. ''way2movies''. 21 August 2014. Retrieved 2 September 2014.</ref>

The soundtrack received mixed reviews from critics. ''Behindwoods'' wrote, "''Vanmam'' - de-ja-vu of Thaman’s earlier albums", and rated the album 1.75/5.<ref>[http://www.behindwoods.com/tamil-movies/vanmam/vanmam-songs-review.html "VANMAM SONGS REVIEW"]. ''Behindwoods''. 1 September 2014. Retrieved 2 September 2014.</ref> M. K. Surendhar of ''Onlykollywood'' gave 2.35/5 and concluded, "Thaman's lacklustre run in Kollywood continues while he's soaring heights in Tollywood."<ref>M. K. Surendhar (2 September 2014). [http://www.onlykollywood.com/vanmam-songs-review/ "Vanmam Songs Review"]. ''Onlykollywood''. Retrieved 2 September 2014.</ref> ''Indiaglitz'' wrote, "Thaman's last release ''Meaghamann'' is a cool album with just 3 songs and a theme track. He has dished out a similar stuff in ''Vanmam''."<ref>[http://www.indiaglitz.com/channels/tamil/musicreview/18786.html "Vanmam - One more short and sweet album from, Thaman"]. ''Indiaglitz''. 5 September 2014. Retrieved 5 September 2014.</ref> Karthik of ''Milliblog'' wrote, "But for occasional inventiveness, this familiar, predictable output from Thaman is distressing."<ref>Karthik (2 September 2014). [http://itwofs.com/milliblog/2014/09/02/vanmam-music-review-tamil-thaman/ "Vanmam (Music review), Tamil – Thaman"]. ''Milliblog''. Retrieved 5 September 2014.</ref> Siddarth Srinivas of ''Cinemalead'' gave 2 out of 5 and concluded, "Though the autotune tsunami bashes this album to an extent, Thaman has come up with decent songs in "Manamae" and "Aetti Enga Porae". The saturation point has been breached for the composer, and its high time he comes up with innovative music. Otherwise, he better stick to the Telugu industry where he is a celebrated figure!"<ref>Srinivas, Siddarth (2 September 2014). [http://www.cinemalead.com/musicreview-id-vanhmam-aka-vanmham-aka-vanmam-music-review-music-review357.htm "VANMHAM AKA VANMAM MUSIC REVIEW"]. ''Cinemalead''. Retrieved 5 September 2014.</ref>

